cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.algorithm
Class BaseAlgorithm

java.lang.Object
  cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.algorithm.BaseAlgorithm
All Implemented Interfaces:
Algorithm
Direct Known Subclasses:
GeneticAlgorithm, GraphSearch, SimulatedAnnealing
public abstract class BaseAlgorithm
extends java.lang.Object
implements Algorithm

Implements some methods of Algorithm identical for most algorithms.

Reduces work required to add new algorithm by implementing methods which are identical for most algorithms.

Note that to algorithms are considered equal if they are of same class (eg. getClass().equals(this.getClass()) equals) and their labels are equal.

setLabel

public void setLabel(java.lang.String label)
Description copied from interface: Algorithm
Sets label for algorithm.

Note that label is important because ResultEntry uses it to distinguish between different settings of same algorithm.

This should be called automatically in constructor (and no later than in Algorithm.init(cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem.ObjectiveProblem), because Solver might need to override it.

Specified by:
setLabel in interface Algorithm
Parameters:
label - new label for algorithm
